{"title": "Human Nature And Conduct - Part 1, The Place of Habit in Conduct", "description": "John Dewey, an early 20th Century American philosopher, psychologist, educational theorist saw Social Psychology as much a physical science (with rules and predictive power) as Biology and Chemistry. This project encompasses Part 1 of 4 of his book Human Nature and Conduct.<br><br>\n\nDewey's uses the word \"HABIT\" as a specialized catch-all word to describe how a person and his/her objective environment interact. This interaction is the basis for moral judgement. Dewey writes: \"All habits are demands for certain kinds of activity; and they constitute the self.\u201d In other places he also asserts that \"Habits are Will.\" - Summary by William Jones, Soloist", "duration": 9839, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1977", "name": "John Dewey"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/humannatureconduct1_1807_librivox/humannatureandconduct_1807.jpg", "copyright_year": "1922", "genres": ["Philosophy", "Psychology", "Social Science (Culture & Anthropology)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "William Allan Jones"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Michele Fry"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Rapunzelina"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Michele Fry"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [10996], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/humannatureconduct1_1807_librivox/humannatureandconduct1_0_dewey_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1469}, {"section": 1, "title": "1: Habits as Social Functions", "readers": [10996], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/humannatureconduct1_1807_librivox/humannatureandconduct1_1_dewey_64kb.mp3", "duration": 978}, {"section": 2, "title": "2: Habits and Will", "readers": [10996], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/humannatureconduct1_1807_librivox/humannatureandconduct1_2_dewey_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2185}, {"section": 3, "title": "3: Character and Conduct", "readers": [10996], "